dmca.title: BRAINWASH TRADEMARK INFRINGEMENT
dmca.body:
August 31, 1999

AIRBOURNE EXPRESS
[Private]

RE: BRAINWASH TRADEMARK INFRINGMENT

Dear [Private]:

Please be advised that I represent the owners of the registered trademark "Brainwash" concerning your use of that name in a matter that infringes upon that trademark.

On behalf of my client, I herby reassert the demand, originally presented by me in my letter to you as of May 6, 1999, that you stop all use of the domain name "Brainwassh.com" [sic] as it infringes upon my clients registered trademark.

Your wrongful use of my client's trademark "Brainwash" in your registered domain name "Brainwash.com" deprives my client of the use of its registered trademark for advertising purposes, and is likely to cause confusion or mistake.

You are again requested to stop all use of the domain name "Brainwash.com" immediately.

Very truly yours,

[Private]
